SPAIN DAYBOOK: Bankinter, European Summit, ETA Ends Violence

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-10-21T05:40:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-21/spain-daybook-bankinter-european-summit-eta-ends-violence.html
Bankinter SA will publish nine-month
results, while the Spanish mortgage association publishes
mortgage lending data for August.  WHAT TO WATCH:  * Spain ’s Cabinet will hold a meeting followed by a press
conference at around 1:30 p.m. in Madrid. Basque terror group
ETA, which has killed more than 800 people in a four-decade
fight for independence from Spain, announced an end to violence
in a written and videoed statement posted on the website of
Basque newspaper Gara, the habitual channel for the movement’s
declarations.  ECONOMY:  * Volker Kauder , head of the parliamentary group of
Chancellor Angela Merkel’s  Christian Democrats , said “there
will be another summit” of European Union leaders “next week”
Bild-Zeitung reported today. EU leaders already plan to meet on
Oct. 23 in Brussels. Bild didn’t name a date for a possible
additional EU summit.  EQUITIES:  *Luis del Rivero was dismissed yesterday as chairman of
Sacyr Vallehermoso SA after a board meeting.  *Bankinter SA reports nine-month earnings before markets
open.  MARKETS:  *The IBEX 35 Index dropped 2.7 percent to 8,608.2.  *The spread between Spanish and German 10-year borrowing
costs widened to 353.3 basis points.  To contact the reporter on this story:
